{{zh-forms|[[神龙见首不见尾]]|[[神]][[龍]][[見]][[首]][[不]][[見]][[尾]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
Literally: one can see the head of a heavenly dragon, but not the tail
===Idiom===
{{PAGENAME}} (''[[Pinyin]]'' shén lóng jiàn shŏu bù jiàn wĕi)
# to maintain an air of mystery, to not reveal oneself; to play cat and mouse; to remain aloof
#* '''2004:''' 郭凯 ''ed.'' (Guo Kai), ''[http://sports.people.com.cn/GB/31928/32031/33766/33768/2506484.html 飞人“神龙见首不见尾” 乔丹没给中国男篮面子]'' (His Airness "is a no where to be found," [[w:Michael Jordan|Michael Jordan]] disses Chinese basketball players)
#*: ''[[在]][[昨晚]][[從]][[廣東]][[抵達]][[北京]][[後]]，[[喬丹]][[也]][[始終]][[採取]]“'''神龍見首不見尾'''”[[的]][[模式]][[與]][[一]][[干]][[中國]][[媒體]][[和]][[中國]][[球迷]][[捉迷藏]]。''
#*:: ''From the time [[w:Michael Jordan|Michael Jordan]] arrived in Beijing from Guangdong, he took the approach of '''remaining aloof''', and played hide and seek with a slew of Chinese Media and fans.''

